items.body:
I'm fairly new to programming world.
I'm trying to create an Intent with API using python.
My intention is to create an intent from API which can

take training phrases
prompt for parameters inputs from user
fullfillment enabled for the intent
Example:

Intent_Display_Name = 'GetNameFromID'
Training Phrases = ['What is the name of the employee who's id is 6',"Please get name for ID 6"]

for this I'm able to create the intents as below in python.

def create_intent(project_id, display_name, training_phrases_parts,
message_texts):
"""Create an intent of the given intent type."""
import dialogflow_v2 as dialogflow
intents_client = dialogflow.IntentsClient()

parent = intents_client.project_agent_path(project_id)
training_phrases = []
for training_phrases_part in training_phrases_parts:
    part = dialogflow.types.Intent.TrainingPhrase.Part(
        text=training_phrases_part)
    # Here we create a new training phrase for each provided part.
    training_phrase = dialogflow.types.Intent.TrainingPhrase(parts=[part])
    training_phrases.append(training_phrase)

text = dialogflow.types.Intent.Message.Text(text=message_texts)
message = dialogflow.types.Intent.Message(text=text)

intent = dialogflow.types.Intent(
    display_name=display_name,
    training_phrases=training_phrases,
    messages=[message])

response = intents_client.create_intent(parent, intent)

print('Intent created: {}'.format(response))
project_id = 'project_id'
display_name = 'GetNameFromID'
training_phrases_parts = ["What is the name of the employee who's id is 6","please get id"]
message_texts = [" Sure, getting the id for the name"]
create_intent(project_id,display_name,training_phrases_parts,message_texts)

My problem is:

I'm able to :
Create intent with training phrases
But, I'm unable to:
Extract the ID as a parameter from the user.
Enable the fulfilment from API
Please help me.

Thanks.

labels.name: api: dialogflow
labels.description: Issues related to the dialogflow-python-client-v2 API.

items.body:
**Environment details:**
OS type and version: Ubuntu 18.04.4 LTS
Python version and virtual environment information: Python 3.6.9
dialogflow version: Latest

I'm trying to add training phrases to a Follow Up intent. Here is my code:

```
def list_intents(project_id, client, parent):
    intents = client.list_intents(parent)
    dict_intents = {}
    for intent in intents:
        dict_intents[intent.name] = intent.display_name
    return dict_intents


def update_intent(project_id, intent_name, training_phrases_parts):
    client = dialogflow.IntentsClient()
    parent = client.project_agent_path(project_id)
    intent_path = ''
    dict_intents = list_intents(project_id, client, parent)
    for key, value in dict_intents.items():
        if value == intent_name:
            intent_path = key
    intent = client.get_intent(
        intent_path, intent_view=dialogflow.enums.IntentView.INTENT_VIEW_FULL)
    training_phrases = []
    for training_phrases_part in training_phrases_parts:
        part = dialogflow.types.Intent.TrainingPhrase.Part(
            text=training_phrases_part)
        training_phrase = dialogflow.types.Intent.TrainingPhrase(parts=[part])
        training_phrases.append(training_phrase)
    intent.training_phrases.extend(training_phrases)
    response = client.update_intent(intent)
    return 'Updated'
```

But I get this error:

`InvalidArgument: 400 com.google.apps.framework.request.BadRequestException: Read-only field 'root_followup_intent_name' cannot be set.`

This code works fine with regular intents but when I try to update a Follow Up Intent it fails...
Any idea what I should do? Any suggestion?

items.title: Fail to finish an intents using python API

labels.name: api: dialogflow
labels.description: Issues related to the dialogflow-python-client-v2 API.

items.body:
#### Environment details

1. OS type and version: Windows 10 Home Edition
2. Python: 3.6.1
3. dialogflow version:  0.8.0

#### Steps to reproduce

1. Create an agent and it's intents in dialogflow web UI
2. Implement get_response() function by dialogflow_v2 package
3. run the following code

#### Code example

```python=
import os
import dialogflow_v2 as dialogflow

os.environ["GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS"] = <api_credentials_path.json>
project_id = <my_project_id>
session_id = '81000003031'  # Just an example

session_client = dialogflow.SessionsClient()
session = self.session_client.session_path(project_id , session_id)

def get_response(query):
    text_input = dialogflow.types.TextInput(text=query, language_code='zh-TW')
    query_input = dialogflow.types.QueryInput(text=text_input)
    response = session_client.detect_intent(session=session, query_input=query_input)
    return response

if __name__ == '__main__':
    while True:
        query = input('Query:')
        response = dialogflow_api.get_response(query)
        print(response)
```

#### Problem

Hi,
I encountered an issue that it always fail to recognize the last entity after I trigger an intent and fulfill all other entities, the ```get_response()``` function should return "Text Response" which I just define but it returns the default fallback intent response instead. However, It successfully return the "Text Response" when testing on dialogflow webUI. 

For example: 
+ Intent: Reserve meeting room
+ Entity to fulfill: time & room number
+ User defined entity: room-number (A101)

Test on dialogflow UI (success):
```
I want to reserve a meeting room
-> When?
9:00am
-> Which room?
A101
-> Ok, your reservation is accepted
```

Test on my code (fail):
```
I want to reserve a meeting room
-> When?
9:00am
-> Which room?
A101
-> I can't understand
```

```
I want to reserve a meeting room A101
-> When?
9:00am
-> I can't understand
```

Would you may know how to fix this issue?
Thank you very much for helping

I'm having a bit of trouble with the retry/timeout behaviour of `train_agent` currently. To debug that, I configured my log level to debug and I get the following output:
```
DEBUG:google.api_core.retry:Retrying due to , sleeping 0.6s ...
DEBUG:google.api_core.retry:Retrying due to , sleeping 3.7s ...
```
Needless to say that the `due to ,` part is a little unsatisfying and not too helpful :D

I'm using V2 (not beta) on Linux, using the most recent version of the library on pip (`0.7.2`) for Python 3.7.

No special steps are needed to reproduce. Just prepare an agent with a few intents and some example utterances, create a Python script and set the log level of `logging` to `DEBUG` and call `train_agent` on that agent. You will most likely get at least one of the log lines above.

items.body:
DialogFlow environments allows users to publish different versions of their agent.

The Python SDK should add an argument to the [detect_intent_texts](https://github.com/dialogflow/dialogflow-python-client-v2/blob/master/samples/detect_intent_texts.py) that specifies the version of the agent that they wish to use.

For example, a user may wish to publish a version of their agent that does not call the fulfillment webhook with each request. This is a great DialogFlow feature. But, unless the SDK is updated to be able to specify the version of the agent, the feature can't be used.

According to the documentation [`SessionsClient.detect_intent`](http://dialogflow-python-client-v2.readthedocs.io/en/latest/gapic/v2beta1/api.html#dialogflow_v2beta1.SessionsClient.detect_intent) should work with a dict as the query_input. The docs don't say what keys must be in that dict, but assuming they are the same as in the `dialogflow_v2beta1.types.QueryInput` classes I tried this example (which is taken almost word for word from the documentation):

```
$ ipython
Python 3.6.4 (default, Jan  6 2018, 11:51:59) 
Type 'copyright', 'credits' or 'license' for more information
IPython 6.3.0 -- An enhanced Interactive Python. Type '?' for help.

In [1]: from dialogflow_v2beta1 import SessionsClient

In [2]: client = SessionsClient()

In [3]: session = client.session_path('MY_AGENT', 'abcdefg123')

In [4]: query_input = {'text': 'talk to MY_AGENT', 'language_code': 'en-US'}

In [5]: response = client.detect_intent(session, query_input)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
TypeError                                 Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-5-b6d5f075ffb7> in <module>()
----> 1 response = client.detect_intent(session, query_input)

~/<project_dir>/venv/lib/python3.6/site-packages/dialogflow_v2beta1/gapic/sessions_client.py in detect_intent(self, session, query_input, query_params, input_audio, retry, timeout)
    202             query_input=query_input,
    203             query_params=query_params,
--> 204             input_audio=input_audio)
    205         return self._detect_intent(request, retry=retry, timeout=timeout)
    206 

TypeError: Parameter to MergeFrom() must be instance of same class: expected google.cloud.dialogflow.v2beta1.TextInput got str.
```

Wrapping the input in a `dialogflow.v2beta1.types.QueryInput` works, but that requires two additional object instantiations and should not be necessary according to the current documentation.
